5. Transformation algebra

Emotions are not static. They move.

So define transformations as operators.

Example operators
	•	Integration
fear → courage
	•	Collapse
fear → apathy
	•	Activation
apathy → courage
	•	Diffusion
hate → sadness / exhaustion
	•	Binding
anxiety + purpose → vigilance
	•	Splitting
shame → anger + withdrawal
	•	Translation
one culture’s “honor” emotion into another culture’s nearest equivalent
	•	Anchoring
panic → grounded alertness
	•	Redirection
envy → aspiration

This fits your larger Transformation Alphabet naturally.

